Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three (3) years.   Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision.  Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Repay $50.00 buy money; 
2) AODA assessment and follow through counseling; 
3) Obtain mental health assessment and follow through;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
5) Use only one doctor for prescriptions and only one pharmacy to fill prescriptions;
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination.  
Court finds defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.  
Defendant is given 124 days sentence credit.   
Minutes.
